[title]
Check if numad rpm package is installed and numad daemon is running

[description]
The 2 checks are important to ascertain if numad rpm is installed and started.

1. Check if numad rpm is installed.
2. Check if numad daemon is currently running.

	User-level daemon that monitors NUMA topology and processes resource consumption to facilitate good NUMA resource alignment of applications/virtual machines to improve performance and minimize cost of remote memory latencies.

